{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EXUBSiPXNuTZ2Fo7xnrjop","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LHPVDyJwC1j2LTcPiAZXMH","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Session retrospective","prompt":"Run /retrospective for the current sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. This file contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nThis is session 9 of the day (2026-03-25). The session was a NO_WORK result — no actionable stories remain. 65/66 stories are done. The only remaining story (14-4-observability-backend-choice) is flagged for skipping due to retry exhaustion (7 retries, operator-flagged).\n\nSessions 7, 8, and 9 were all no-ops for the same reason. This is the key observation — Ralph keeps spawning sessions that have nothing to do.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - The repeated no-op sessions (7, 8, 9) indicate Ralph needs a \"sprint complete\" signal\n   - 14-4-observability-backend-choice has been stuck at verifying for many sessions\n   - Docker keychain issues blocked verification in earlier sessions\n3. **What went well** — 65/66 stories completed (98.5% completion rate), sprint nearly done\n4. **What went wrong** — repeated no-op sessions wasting API budget, 14-4 stuck\n5. **Lessons learned** — Ralph should detect \"no actionable work\" and stop spawning sessions\n6. **Action items** — concrete next steps:\n   - Fix now: Ralph should have a circuit breaker for consecutive NO_WORK results\n   - Fix soon: Resolve 14-4 manually or accept it as blocked\n   - Backlog: Improve Docker keychain handling for non-interactive sessions\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":471,"cache_read_input_tokens":40303,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":471},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65b504c2-5448-4f8c-9d4a-25ffec314d5a","uuid":"35393921-809e-40af-ac3f-0038bf019163"}
